Polycom (R) SoundPoint(R) IP, SoundStation(R) IP and VVX (TM) Software Release SIP 3.2.2

This release is a SIP patch release applicable to all currently shipping SoundPoint IP, SoundStation IP products deployed 
on SIP networks. For the VVX1500 product this release is a feature upgrade release (SIP 3.2.0 and SIP 3.2.1 releases 
include the SIP 3.1.3 variant for the VVX1500). There is significant new functionality included in thhis release for VVX1500 
only. See the Release Notes for more details.

WARNINGS:  
1. VVX1500 products that are upgraded to SIP 3.2.2 WILL NOT BE ABLE TO DOWNGRADE TO EARLIER RELEASES.
2. The distribution files for the VVX1500 product contain both the BootROM and SIP software since there are inter-dependcies
that require both to be upgraded at the same time.
3. The SoundPoint IP 300, 301, 500, 600, 601 and SoundStation IP 4000 products are not supported in this release. 
Customers that are upgrading to this release and have any of these phones deployed on their network should refer to 
technical bulletin 35311 for information on methods to configure the phones. 
This Technical Bulletin is available from the Support site http://www.polycom.com/support/voice/soundpoint_ip/VoIP_Technical_Bulletins_pub.html
4. This release requires BootROM 4.1.0 or newer to run on the SoundPoint IP 550, 560 and 650 products.


